  "local_port": 37188,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What guidelines are in place regarding passport photos in Canada?",
  "response": "In Canada, there are specific guidelines that must be followed when taking a passport photo. These guidelines are in place to ensure that the photo meets the standards set by Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC) and can be used for official purposes. The following are the key guidelines regarding passport photos in Canada:\n\n1. **Size and format**: The photo must be 50mm x 70mm in size, with the face centered and measuring between 31mm and 36mm from the bottom of the chin to the top of the head. The photo must be in color and printed on high-quality photographic paper.\n\n2. **Quality**: The photo must be clear, well-lit, and in focus. It should not be digitally altered or retouched. The background must be plain and light-colored, with no shadows or other objects visible.\n\n3. **Expression and pose**: The person in the photo must have a neutral expression, with their mouth closed and eyes open and looking directly at the camera. The head must be straight and facing forward, with no tilt or rotation.\n\n4. **Clothing and accessories**: The person in the photo should wear normal street clothing, and no uniforms or camouflage clothing is allowed. Hats and head coverings are not permitted, except for religious or medical reasons. If a head covering is worn, it must not cast shadows on the face.\n\n5. **Glasses**: Glasses are allowed in passport photos, but they must not have tinted lenses or cause glare or shadows. The eyes must be clearly visible through the lenses.\n\n6. **Age and validity**: The photo must be taken within the last six months and reflect the person's current appearance. For children under the age of two, the photo must be taken within the last six months, and for children between the ages of two and 16, the photo must be taken within the last 12 months.\n\n7. **Signature**: The back of the photo must be signed by the person in the photo or, in the case of a child, by the person applying for the passport.\n\nBy following these guidelines, you can ensure that your passport photo meets the standards set by the IRCC and will be accepted for official purposes.",
